system76-driver (14.04.6) trusty; urgency=low

  * As screen revisions within a product lifetime make it too difficult to
    supply a correct color profile out of the box, drop color profile actions
    from bonx7, galu1, gazp9 (note this wont remove profiles already
    installed, will only effect new shipments and re-installs)
  * debian/control: drop Build-Depends/Depends on `python3-dbus`, as it was
    only needed for color-profile actions
  * debian/control: add Depends on `pm-utils` as some driver actions expect
    /etc/pm/power.d/ to exist, which seems not to be installed by default on
    Xubuntu, Ubuntu GNOME
  * Rework GrubAction and its subclasses so that it preserves customer changes
    and can also remove previously added kernel parameters when needed
  * Rework system76-driver-cli to make it more suitable for automatically
    being called from a postinst script
  * Add debian/system76-driver.postinst that automatically calls
    /usr/bin/system76-driver-cli
  * system76-daemon no longer needs to fix caps on /bin/ping, /bin/ping6,
    /usr/bin/arping as the `iputils` package as been updated and reverted to
    use suid again; however, caps fix on /usr/bin/gnome-keyring-daemon is
    still needed
  * Add remove_backlight_vendor action to gazp9, gazp9b to properly remove
    acpi_backlight=vendor from GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT
  * On daru4, replace `grub_daru4` with `backlight_vendor` plus
    `disable_power_well` actions now that GrubAction is cumulative

 -- Jason Gerard DeRose <jason@system76.com>  Fri, 09 May 2014 13:22:25 -0600

